	": Hello sushiw097 and welcome to TASVideos. While your movie appears decently optimized, there are two major issues with it. One it fails to achieve the goal it states to achieve: it performs two glitches instead of one, since it uses Left + Right to save time in one level. The second is that this goal is unacceptable. While usage of fewer glitches could potentially be seen as a valid goal, the usage of one glitch total seems arbitrary. Why one glitch? Why not two or three? There's no real justification for the goal choice here, nor any reason to believe the audience would find this particular goal choice interesting. In order to accept exotic goal choices, they must be seen as unique and entertaining, and this isn't really either. Read the 
	(__wikiLink|displaytext=rules|href=/MovieRules#MovieGoals)
	" for further information on this.
	$LF
